{
  "texts": [
    "The CSA algorithm employs a population-based iterative optimization strategy to build a collection of low-energy conformations that have been locally reduced.",
    "The CSA population strictly adheres to specified mutual distances, which facilitates the concentration of conformational sampling on more profound minima during each iteration.",
    "The process of global optimization encompasses the manipulation of ring conformation and the reconstruction of the internal ligand structure, allowing for the adjustment of many degrees of freedom, such as bond angles and lengths.",
    "GalaxyDock3 has the same energy components as the GalaxyDock BP2 score with additional bonded energy terms to train its hybrid scoring function [22].",
